Coming out of the weekend long ANC NEC meeting this week, the president told the nation, South Africa needs African solutions for African problems in the fight against pandemics and that the ruling party discussed building capacity to enable the country to manufacture its own vaccines in future. Well, in a special hour long documentary, Checkpoint’s Nkepile Mabuse asks the health department why a facility established 17 years ago for that very reason is not playing this critical role of saving lives during a deadly Covid pandemic.